SIMPLE: render
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Render
<hw>Rend"er</hw> <pr>(-?r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Rend</er>.]</ety> <def>One who rends.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Render</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Render
<hw>Ren"der</hw> <pr>(r?n"d?r)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Rendered</conjf> <pr>(-d?rd)</pr>;<pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Rendering</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F. <ets>rendre</ets>,
LL. <ets>rendre</ets>, fr. L. <ets>reddere</ets>; pref. <ets>red-</ets>,
<ets>re-</ets>, re- + <ets>dare</ets> to give. See <er>Date</er>time,
and cf. <er>Reddition</er>, <er>Rent</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
return; to pay back; to restore.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Whose smallest minute lost, no riches <qex>render</qex> may.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To inflict, as a retribution; to requite.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I will <qex>render</qex> vengeance to mine enemies.</q>
<rj><qau>Deut. xxxii. 41.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To give up; to yield; to surrender.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I 'll make her <qex>render</qex> up her page to me.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Hence, to furnish; to contribute.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Logic <qex>renders</qex> its daily service to wisdom and
virtue.</q> <rj><qau>I. Watts.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>To furnish; to state; to deliver; <as>as, to
<ex>render</ex> an account; to <ex>render</ex> judgment</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>To cause to be, or to become; <as>as, to
<ex>render</ex> a person more safe or more unsafe; to <ex>render</ex> a
fortress secure.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>7.</sn> <def>To translate from one language into another; <as>as,
to <ex>render</ex> Latin into English</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>8.</sn> <def>To interpret; to set forth, represent, or exhibit;
<as>as, an actor <ex>renders</ex> his part poorly; a singer
<ex>renders</ex> a passage of music with great effect; a painter
<ex>renders</ex> a scene in a felicitous manner</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He did <qex>render</qex> him the most unnatural⟦br⟧
That lived amongst men.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>9.</sn> <def>To try out or extract (oil, lard, tallow, etc.) from
fatty animal substances; <as>as, to <ex>render</ex>
tallow</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>10.</sn> <def>To plaster, as a wall of masonry, without the use
of lath.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Render</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Render
<hw>Ren"der</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To give an account;
to make explanation or confession.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>To pass; to run; -- said of the
passage of a rope through a block, eyelet, etc.; <as>as, a rope
<ex>renders</ex> well, that is, passes freely</as>; also, to yield or
give way.</def> <rj><au>Totten.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Render</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Render
<hw>Ren"der</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A surrender.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A return; a payment of rent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In those early times the king's household was supported by
specific <qex>renders</qex> of corn and other victuals from the tenants
of the demains.</q> <rj><qau>Blackstone.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>An account given; a statement.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1218 --></p>

<p><ent>Renderable</ent>⟦br⟧
